26 SECTION 9. Confidentiality of individually identifiable information. (1) As used in this
27 section, “individually identifiable information” means any health information in any form or
28 medium that is identifiable to an individual, including demographic information that identi-
29 fies the individual, or for which there is a reasonable basis to believe the information can
30 be used to identify an individual, and that relates to applications for or receipt of legally-
31 protected reproductive or gender-affirming health care activities.
32 (2) Except to the extent an individual consents to the information’s disclosure, the
33 individual’s individually identifiable information obtained by the authority:
34 (a) Is confidential and not subject to disclosure under ORS 192.311 to 192.478;
35 (b) May be disclosed only as necessary and directly connected with the administration
36 of the state medical assistance program or the authority’s duties and responsibilities under
37 ORS 435.230; and
38 (c) Is confidential, nondiscoverable and inadmissible in any judicial or administrative
39 proceeding that is not directly connected with the authority’s administration of the state
40 medical assistance program or the programs described in ORS 435.230.
