2 SECTION 16. ORS 687.445 is amended to read:
3 687.445. (1) In the manner prescribed in ORS chapter 183 for contested cases and in consultation
4 with the Health Licensing Office and subject to subsection (2) of this section, the State Board
5 of Direct Entry Midwifery may impose a form of discipline specified in ORS 676.612 and 676.992 (1)
6 and (2) against any person practicing direct entry midwifery for any of the grounds listed in ORS
7 676.612 and for any violation of the provisions of ORS 687.405 to 687.495 or the rules adopted under
8 ORS 687.405 to 687.495.
9 (2) The board may not suspend or revoke a person’s license to practice direct entry
10 midwifery, or refuse to grant a license to a person to practice direct entry midwifery, be-
11 cause of a conviction or disciplinary action resulting solely from the person’s provision of a
12 reproductive or gender-affirming health care service that is otherwise lawful in this state
13 but unlawful in the jurisdiction in which the person provided the service, so long as the
14 service provided was performed in accordance with the standard of care applicable to the
15 service.
