17 MISCELLANEOUS
18
19 SECTION 17. Applicability. The amendments to ORS 33.420 and 33.460 by sections 11 and
20 12 of this 2026 Act apply to an application for change of name, application for legal change
21 of sex or application for simultaneous change of name and legal change of sex that is filed
22 with the court on or after July 1, 2026, and, upon motion of the applicant, to an application
23 for legal change of sex or application for simultaneous change of name and legal change of
24 sex that was filed with the court before July 1, 2026.
25 SECTION 18. Delayed operative date. (1) The amendments to ORS 33.420 and 33.460 by
26 sections 11 and 12 of this 2026 Act become operative on July 1, 2026.
27 (2) The Judicial Department may take any action before the operative date specified in
28 subsection (1) of this section that is necessary to enable the department to exercise, on and
29 after the operative date specified in subsection (1) of this section, all of the duties, functions
30 and powers conferred on the department by the amendments to ORS 33.420 and 33.460 by
31 sections 11 and 12 of this 2026 Act.
32 SECTION 19. Captions. The unit and section captions used in this 2026 Act are provided
33 only for the convenience of the reader and do not become part of the statutory law of this
34 state or express any legislative intent in the enactment of this 2026 Act.
35 SECTION 20. Emergency. This 2026 Act being necessary for the immediate preservation
36 of the public peace, health and safety, an emergency is declared to exist, and this 2026 Act
37 takes effect on its passage.
